# Cross-platform line-ending policy.
#
# Source lives on Windows (D:\) and is built from both WSL (GCC) and Windows
# (MSVC). Normalize every text file to LF in the repo AND the working tree so
# WSL and Windows checkouts stay byte-identical — no CRLF/LF churn when the dev
# host switches. See CLAUDE.md「构建环境与跨平台约束」.
* text=auto eol=lf

# --- Explicit text types (belt-and-suspenders over text=auto) ---
*.cpp          text eol=lf
*.h            text eol=lf
*.hpp          text eol=lf
*.c            text eol=lf
*.hlsl         text eol=lf
*.ts           text eol=lf
*.tsx          text eol=lf
*.js           text eol=lf
*.json         text eol=lf
*.tmj          text eol=lf
*.cmake        text eol=lf
CMakeLists.txt text eol=lf
*.md           text eol=lf
*.css          text eol=lf
*.html         text eol=lf
*.py           text eol=lf
*.sh           text eol=lf

# --- Windows-only scripts must keep CRLF to run under cmd.exe ---
*.bat          text eol=crlf
*.cmd          text eol=crlf
# PowerShell tolerates LF, so it follows the global LF policy above.

# --- Binary assets: never normalize line endings, never diff as text ---
*.png          binary
*.jpg          binary
*.jpeg         binary
*.gif          binary
*.ico          binary
*.bmp          binary
*.tga          binary
*.dds          binary
*.ttf          binary
*.otf          binary
*.wav          binary
*.ogg          binary
*.mp3          binary
*.cso          binary
*.bin          binary
